Uganda is the third largest refugee hosting country in the world, hosting over 1.29 million refguees and aslyum seekers. South Sudan and the Democratic Repbulic of the Congo are the top two countries of origin in the region with close to 1.2 million Congolese and South Sudanese seeking refuge in Uganda.
